# onnxruntime-node and @huggingface/transformers are marked `external` in
# esbuild.js (native binaries can't be bundled into a single JS file), so all
# of their transitive node_modules content must ship as real files. That
# transitive tree is deep (protobufjs, flatbuffers, onnxruntime-common, etc.)
# — surgical per-package whitelisting here missed real dependencies twice
# during testing, so node_modules ships in full except the one package
# empirically confirmed unused for our Node/text-classification path
# (verified by removing it and re-running classification successfully): if
# @huggingface/transformers is ever upgraded, re-verify this still holds.
node_modules/onnxruntime-web/**
